From: VyOS ARM64 Build <build@vyos.io>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix fmlib/kernel ABI mismatch in t_FmPcdHashTableParams

The ASK kernel patch added agingSupport, externalHash, and
externalHashParams fields to t_FmPcdHashTableParams in the kernel header.
However, the ASK fmlib patch does NOT add these fields to its copy of
the struct. This creates an ABI mismatch:

  Kernel struct: {base, ccNextEngineParamsForMiss, agingSupport,
                  externalHash, externalHashParams, table_type, IPR}
  Fmlib struct:  {base, ccNextEngineParamsForMiss, table_type, IPR}

The ioctl handler's copy_to_user() writes the larger kernel struct back
to fmlib's smaller buffer, overflowing into heap metadata and causing:
  malloc_consolidate(): invalid chunk size (SIGABRT)

Additionally, the IOC wrapper struct (ioc_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t in
fm_pcd_ioctls.h) and the compat struct (ioc_compat_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t
in lnxwrp_ioctls_fm_compat.h) must also have these fields removed to
satisfy the ASSERT_COND in LnxWrpPCDIOCTLTypeChecking (line 380):
  sizeof(ioc_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t) == sizeof(t_FmPcdHashTableParams) + sizeof(void *)

Without fixing the IOC struct, the kernel panics at boot with ASSERT_COND
failure in lnxwrp_ioctls_fm.c:380.

Fix: Remove the three unused fields from all three structs. They are
dead code because:
- agingSupport: ExternalHashTableSet always enables timestamps
  (the check is commented out in fm_ehash.c:886)
- externalHash: The redirect uses #ifdef USE_ENHANCED_EHASH, not this
  runtime field
- externalHashParams: dataMemId/dataLiodnOffs are commented out in
  ExternalHashTableSet (fm_ehash.c:883-884)

Files modified:
- drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/inc/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h
  (t_FmPcdHashTableParams — kernel internal struct)
- include/uapi/linux/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ioctls.h
  (ioc_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t — UAPI ioctl struct)
- drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/src/wrapper/lnxwrp_ioctls_fm_compat.h
  (ioc_compat_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t — 32-bit compat struct)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/inc/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/inc/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ext.h
@@ (t_FmPcdHashTableParams struct)
 
-    bool                                agingSupport;
-    bool                                externalHash;
-    struct {
-        uint8_t                         dataMemId;
-        uint32_t                        dataLiodnOffs;
-    }                                   externalHashParams;
     e_FmPcdHashTableType                table_type;

--- a/include/uapi/linux/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ioctls.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/fmd/Peripherals/fm_pcd_ioctls.h
@@ (ioc_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t struct)
 
-boolaging_support;
-(multiline comment block removed)
-
-#if (DPAA_VERSION >= 11)
-boolexternal_hash;
+(comment noting fields removed)
 #ifndef EXCLUDE_FMAN_IPR_OFFLOAD
  ... (table_type and IPR fields kept)
 #endif
-
-struct {
-uint8_tdata_mem_id;
-uint16_tdata_liodn_offs;
-uintptr_tmiss_monitor_addr;
-} external_hash_params;
 #endif /* (DPAA_VERSION >= 11) */

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/src/wrapper/lnxwrp_ioctls_fm_compat.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/src/wrapper/lnxwrp_ioctls_fm_compat.h
@@ (ioc_compat_fm_pcd_hash_table_params_t struct)
 
-boolaging_support;
-boolexternal_hash;
-struct {
-uint8_tdata_mem_id;
-uint16_tdata_liodn_offs;
-compat_uptr_tmiss_monitor_addr;
-} external_hash_params;
+(comment noting fields removed)
     compat_uptr_t               id;